reviews.review_text: new stuff Not only was this night the debut of Althea, Lost Sailor, and Jerry's Tiger guitar, but (according to Blair Jackson's gear book) of a new PA setup that was a substantial improvement over the past few years.  I dig the feel of being 40' from the stage, and while this aud won't convert any sbd snobs, I feel that the mighty Playin space meltdown translates much better this way than on the sbd.

on the fence I agree with the nwgj with regards to the PITB.  There is a nice feel on this capture during the Shakedown > PITB.  
As for the rest of the show, Severson only being 40' w/ some quality mics I'd expect a better recording. Not his best work.  Its distant at times & muddy at others.
